  "2026-07-13T16:41:21.707Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,"Review evidence: dangling-reference merge now trims and lowercases reference.kind for both duplicate comparison and inserted edge identity. A stored uppercase RELATED dangling edge remains one canonical related edge. Focused tests and exact full coverage pass."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T15:28:06.747Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,"Delete-parent behavior was evaluated. This PR keeps delete permissive for history and migration compatibility, while making every deps projection surface the resulting typed missing edge; a future delete guard should be separately governed if policy changes."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T15:28:08.908Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,Dependency projections must consume the same dangling-reference classifier as governance validation; rebuilding only from resolvable structured edges silently erases missing hierarchy context.
  "2026-07-13T16:15:50.427Z",codex-sdk-contracts-20260713,Normalize case at dependency graph identity boundaries while preserving canonical item ids in output; malformed persisted records remain the item parser/store boundary's responsibility.
